output.map_title: Map to show the number of graduates of Medicine and dentistry now working in Education who studied in each region five years after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2018/19 tax year.
output.maptext: For first degree graduates of Medicine and dentistry in the Education industry five years after graduation, the regions where the most graduates had studied were London, North West and Yorkshire and the Humber. The regions where the fewest graduates had studied were East Midlands, North East, South West and West Midlands. The regions where the highest number of graduates lived five years after graduation were East of England, London and North West and the regions where the fewest graduates lived were East Midlands, North East, South East, South West, West Midlands and Yorkshire and the Humber.
output.maptext2: For first degree graduates of Medicine and dentistry in the Education industry, the region with the most graduates living there five years after graduation, compared to the number having studied in the region was East of England, where the number of graduates was the same as the number of students.The regions with the largest decrease were South East and Yorkshire and the Humber where the number of graduates decreased by -100%.
